    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(center)">charge to my yr</p>
            <p>Rd Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Be good enough and send to my address an extra weekly marked<lb/> F
                W, commencing with the first no. x The <persName>Rd Mr Cohen</persName><lb/> Editor
                of the Israelitish Volks friend of which I send you a <del>no</del> copy<lb/> is
                desirous of exchanging with you, price same as yours, if<lb/> you send him the 1.
                &amp; 2d he will know that you accept his terms<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. Holzman</persName> of <placeName>Main St</placeName> does not
                    <sic>reve</sic> his papers regularly he wishes<lb/> you to look to it for him.
                The enclosed packet is an attempt<lb/> to answer an Ar. In the Israelite of
                    <date>April 1.</date> in which he <persName>D. W</persName> has attacked<lb/> me
                very much unbecoming a Gentlm. And a minister. I had written it, with the<lb/>
                intention of answering him through one of our Daily Papers but my family<lb/> has
                persuaded me otherways, it is <sic>there</sic> opinion that had <persName>Dr.
                    Wise</persName> meant<lb/> well he should have sent his rejoinder through the
                Occident, which <sic>offerd</sic><lb/> its papers for that purpose, but he well
                knows, that there are many<lb/> who read the <del>Occid</del> Israelite never see
                the Occidt. Thus he has it all his<lb/> own way. I have <sic>culld</sic> some of the
                sentences from some of the Articles<lb/> in the Occidet. <del>thinking</del> as I
                intended it for a strange paper they the public<lb/> would have had some information
                regarding the erratic course of the Israelite<lb/> however if you think proper to
                publish my rejoinder, subject to yr<lb/> correction and then send a few <hi
                    rend="underline">copies</hi> here. I will get them filed in<lb/> all the reading
                rooms of this place in company with the Israelite</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">We have <sic>finaly</sic> adopted the German Minag it has
                displaced<lb/> only 2 persons namely <persName>I. Hershberg</persName> and a
                    <persName>Mr. Samuels</persName>
                <del>who</del> They have <add>?</add><lb/> we can well dispense with them, the
                former in particular who is <sic>realy</sic> a<lb/> very <sic>quarelsome</sic>
                disposed man, the majority in these cases will rule<lb/> but the change will greatly
                increase our members.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I write this at the Bake House where we are now making<lb/> Matses.
                    <persName>Mr. Hyman Moses</persName> &amp; my self are superintending the<lb/>
                work which is troublesome it is only 11 years ago that 60 Barrels<lb/> of Flour was
                more than a sufficient for <placeName>Cincint</placeName> &amp; neighborhood<lb/>
                and now 360 is not enough—our small congregation will make at<lb/> least this
                    y<del>or</del>ear 80 Barrels into Matses I shall have an occasion to<lb/>
                <del>write</del> write shortly again my rejoinder needs no comment from me as
                it<lb/> speaks for itself Respy yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">S Bruel</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <addressee>Rd I Leeser</addressee>
                <date>8. April 59</date>
            </p>
        </body>
